item.title: Wtf.?
item.dc:creator: @Oh-Noes Oh-Noes
item.description:
@Oh-Noes wrote:

In item.java, search for

"data/sellable.dat"

You should find the something like the following:

try { FileInputStream dataIn = new FileInputStream(new File( "data/sellable.dat")); while ((c = dataIn.read()) != -1) { if (c == 0) itemSellable[counter] = true; else itemSellable[counter] = false; counter++; } dataIn.close(); //YOU CAN DEFINE SELLABLE ITEMS HERE } catch (IOException e) { System.out.println("Critical error while loading sellable! Trace:"); e.printStackTrace(); } }
In the space where I’ve typed

//YOU CAN DEFINE SELLABLE ITEMS HERE

Enter the following to make an item sellable:

itemSellable[ITEMIDHERE] = true;

Similarly, you can make it false to make an item unsellable. That should work. Tell me if it doesn’t.
